Indian Hotels Data Analysis Project -
This project focuses on collecting and analyzing hotel data from India using web scraping and data science techniques.

Project Overview -
The goal of this project is to understand the hospitality market in India by looking at hotel prices, ratings, and locations across various cities.

What’s Inside:
Web Scraping: A Jupyter notebook that uses Selenium and BeautifulSoup to automatically collect real-time hotel data (names, prices, and ratings) from the Yatra website.
Data Cleaning & EDA: A notebook dedicated to cleaning the raw data, handling missing values, and performing Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to find trends, such as price distributions by city.
Datasets: The repository includes CSV files containing hotel details for several major Indian cities.

Technologies Used:
Python: The core programming language.
Selenium & BeautifulSoup: For web scraping.
Pandas & NumPy: For data manipulation and cleaning.
Matplotlib & Seaborn: For data visualization.
